ROUTE-AWARE CLINICAL KNOWLEDGE LOADER - 2026-05-15
========================================================================

## CBT / cbt_stage_3_distortions
Route: CBT
Stage task: Name one thinking trap gently without arguing against it yet.
Micro-skills:
- normalize automatic thoughts
- name one likely distortion
- ask whether the label fits
Avoid:
- deep evidence testing
- asking generic feelings questions
- using several distortion labels at once

## MBI / mbi_stage_1_grounding
Route: MBI
Stage task: Stabilize acute overload through present-moment anchoring before any analysis.
Micro-skills:
- paced exhale
- feet-on-floor anchoring
- one-sense orientation
- short body contact cue
Avoid:
- cognitive disputation
- asking for evidence

## MBI / mbi_stage_2_decentering
Route: MBI
Stage task: Help the user observe thoughts as mental events without debating them.
Micro-skills:
- thought labeling
- decentering phrase
- noticing without arguing
- returning to breath or senses
Avoid:
- proving the thought wrong
- naming CBT distortions

## BA / ba_stage_1_energy_check
Route: BA
Stage task: Validate depletion and measure current energy before selecting action.
Micro-skills:
- depletion validation
- energy rating
- shame reduction
- behavioral framing
Avoid:
- calling the user lazy
- deep cognitive analysis

## BA / ba_stage_3_barrier_schedule
Route: BA
Stage task: Identify the main barrier and schedule the tiny action.
Micro-skills:
- barrier naming
- implementation intention
- time cue
- environment cue
Avoid:
- saying just try harder
- leaving the action unscheduled

